This paper deals with natural language processing tasks, specifically sequence labeling, using contextualized embeddings such as ELMo and BERT. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses fine-tuning and adaptation of embeddings, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning techniques, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed approach to text from different domains, which could fall under computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) as it involves analyzing and processing textual data.
